<i>Control Center,
this is Stillwell 1215.</i>

02:11.913 --> 02:13.346
Go ahead, Stillwell 1215.

02:13.515 --> 02:15.813
I'm about four cars
out of 57th Street station...

02:15.984 --> 02:17.747
...being delayed
by a red signal light.

02:20.155 --> 02:21.622
Should be green, Stillwell 1215.

02:21.790 --> 02:23.848
Yeah, tell me something
I don't already know.

02:24.658 --> 02:27.856
All right, roll through it slow,
extreme caution, per the rulebook.

02:39.473 --> 02:42.806
Yeah, cracked rail. Nine-hundred feet
from the east end of the platform.

02:42.976 --> 02:45.467
It's the goddamn cold.
Metal contracts, you know that.

02:45.646 --> 02:47.773
I got it, I got it.
How long it take to fix it?

02:47.948 --> 02:50.041
Gotta put a plate on it. Two hours.

02:51.285 --> 02:53.981
Thank you. Make it an hour and a half,
I'll buy you a beer.

03:23.983 --> 03:27.248
Shit, G.B. I hate to see you
down here on the floor, man.

03:27.420 --> 03:31.081
Temporary, baby. I'll be up there
behind the glass before you know it.

03:44.502 --> 03:45.832
I'm gonna need the R train...

03:46.002 --> 03:48.335
...to switch over
to the express tracks at 34th.

03:48.506 --> 03:50.497
- Which express tracks?
- The one that Q uses.

03:50.674 --> 03:53.734
Once they exit the 57th Street,
they can switch over to the F Line.

03:53.911 --> 03:55.003
Straight into Queens.

03:55.179 --> 03:58.615
Once they get to Queens, they switch
back at 36th Street to the R Line.

03:58.783 --> 04:02.946
All you gotta do, suspend the W,
N and R will pick up the slack.

04:48.097 --> 04:49.587
I can't see where I gotta look.

04:49.766 --> 04:52.233
Unlock the door.
Do it now or I'll kill you. Do it.

04:54.269 --> 04:55.293
All right, all right.

05:16.357 --> 05:17.585
Shut up and walk.

05:18.426 --> 05:20.087
First car, go.

05:30.571 --> 05:32.596
See? I told you I could do this.

05:33.207 --> 05:35.471
Big fucking deal,
you did what you said you'd do.

05:52.425 --> 05:54.290
All right.

05:54.461 --> 05:56.929
Five minutes of peace.

06:00.000 --> 06:03.231
- Yeah!
- Nice!

06:03.403 --> 06:05.268
- Nice.
- All right.

06:05.438 --> 06:06.996
There you go.

06:12.412 --> 06:14.141
I'm on the train and I still got you.

06:14.580 --> 06:17.674
<i>- You still got me?
- I got you. What are you doing?</i>

06:17.850 --> 06:19.818
<i>You still got me?</i>

06:21.053 --> 06:23.317
Oh, my God.

06:28.227 --> 06:29.717
Baby? Baby?

07:25.950 --> 07:27.247
Give me the cutting key.

07:28.152 --> 07:29.710
Cutting key.

07:45.835 --> 07:49.601
Control Center calling Pelham 123.
Come in, Pelham 123.

07:50.106 --> 07:52.734
Why did you stop?
You're all green ahead.

07:56.911 --> 07:59.937
<i>Control Center calling Pelham 123.</i>

08:00.815 --> 08:03.283
<i>Control Center calling Pelham 123.</i>

08:03.685 --> 08:05.676
<i>Why did you stop, 123?
You got green ahead.</i>

08:05.854 --> 08:07.719
It's okay.

08:08.790 --> 08:10.882
Life is simple now.

08:11.058 --> 08:13.356
You just gotta do what I say.

08:18.232 --> 08:19.927
Not now, okay?

08:35.049 --> 08:36.278
Where are you from?

08:37.785 --> 08:40.049
- Brooklyn.
- You Irish?

08:40.655 --> 08:41.679
Yeah.

08:42.390 --> 08:44.483
I thought so.

08:45.493 --> 08:48.223
Who's driving Pelham 123?

08:51.966 --> 08:53.695
Maybe something fell on the tracks.

09:39.678 --> 09:41.771
Wait. Are we going backwards?

09:57.329 --> 09:59.729
42nd Street tower,
I got a train wrong-railing...

09:59.898 --> 10:02.765
...on the southbound Lexington
Avenue Line just north of you.

10:04.369 --> 10:07.202
Listen up,
we need to stop and stay in-station.

10:07.372 --> 10:10.466
All southbound locals
just north of the 51 st Street station.

10:10.642 --> 10:13.372
The operator on 123
is Jerry Pollard.

10:13.545 --> 10:16.480
I know Jerry Pollard.
I went to motorman school with Jerry.

10:16.648 --> 10:20.277
Pelham 123,
come in to me, Pelham 123.

10:20.452 --> 10:22.942
Pelham 123, Jerry Pollard,
what's going on down there?

10:23.120 --> 10:26.385
<i>This is Control Center.
What's going on, 123?</i>

10:28.626 --> 10:32.357
Get an express train to go alongside
them, see what we see in the cab.

10:32.530 --> 10:35.966
<i>Yeah, this is South Ferry 105. I can't
get my windshield wiper to turn on.</i>

10:36.133 --> 10:39.568
South Ferry 105, there's a circuit
breaker right behind you for that.

10:39.736 --> 10:41.067
What's going on?

10:41.237 --> 10:43.068
Maestro, what's going on?

11:00.557 --> 11:01.615
- Cop.
- Excuse me.

11:01.791 --> 11:04.157
- Fuck.
- Watch your backs. Watch your backs.

11:04.327 --> 11:05.817
When I say stop, stop it hard.

11:10.968 --> 11:12.491
- Transit Police.
- Stop.

11:25.682 --> 11:27.149
Everybody sit the fuck down!

11:29.351 --> 11:30.443
Down!

11:31.353 --> 11:32.615
Sit the fuck down!

11:32.788 --> 11:35.416
<i>Jesus! We're getting reports
of gunshots down the tunnel.</i>

11:35.591 --> 11:36.922
Sergeant Moran.

11:37.092 --> 11:39.618
- Delgado, let's call off that express.
- Got it.

11:42.498 --> 11:45.365
I'm gonna die.
I'm gonna fucking die, man.

11:45.534 --> 11:46.558
Come on! Hey.

11:46.735 --> 11:49.532
Everybody up! By the window!
Come on, up, up, up!

11:49.704 --> 11:51.331
Stand up! Stand up! Come on!

11:55.076 --> 11:57.544
Move it! Against the window!

11:58.879 --> 12:00.744
What the fuck is going on?

12:00.915 --> 12:03.246
<i>There was a cop. Bashkin shot him.</i>

12:03.416 --> 12:05.179
I think... I think he's dead.

12:05.352 --> 12:07.752
Put Bashkin on
and find your fucking guts!

12:07.921 --> 12:10.116
<i>- Do it!
- Fuck.</i>

12:11.758 --> 12:14.488
<i>- What happened?
- A cop. He's dead.</i>

12:14.928 --> 12:16.088
Put the conductor on.

12:17.831 --> 12:19.923
<i>- What's your name, conductor?
- Regina.</i>

12:20.099 --> 12:22.567
Regina, baby, listen,
you got a job to do, honey.

12:22.735 --> 12:23.759
A job?

12:23.936 --> 12:26.837
God put you on this Earth
for one thing and one thing only.

12:27.006 --> 12:28.975
You conduct those people
off the train...

12:29.142 --> 12:31.667
...up to the platform.
You got that? Let me hear it.

12:31.845 --> 12:33.369
<i>Let me hear you do that.</i>

12:35.514 --> 12:36.538
Listen up, everybody.

12:36.715 --> 12:40.515
We're gonna go back to the platform.
I need everybody to...

12:40.686 --> 12:41.914
<i>Regina. Let's do it again.</i>

12:42.087 --> 12:43.384
Conduct those people.

12:44.757 --> 12:47.590
Listen. Now, we're gonna head back
towards the platform.

12:47.760 --> 12:49.591
I want everybody to slowly get up.

12:49.762 --> 12:52.094
<i>- I'm gonna get you off this train.
- Good.</i>

12:52.264 --> 12:56.098
Now, we're gonna be on the tracks,
so if you don't need it, leave it.

13:08.013 --> 13:09.604
<i>Have been put on alert regarding...</i>

13:09.781 --> 13:12.648
Right here, right here.
Right here, right here.

13:12.817 --> 13:14.513
Cross right here, right here.

13:14.687 --> 13:18.248
- Go.
- Cross over right here, right here.

13:18.424 --> 13:19.448
Let's go.

13:19.625 --> 13:21.923
- Up the stairs, up the stairs.
- Here you go.

13:22.094 --> 13:25.028
- Every cop in the city is on the way.
- Maybe it wasn't gunshots.

13:25.196 --> 13:27.664
Train could be blowing breakers.
Or the motor blew?

13:27.832 --> 13:30.027
No, this is on purpose.

13:30.902 --> 13:32.233
Fuck you.

13:32.403 --> 13:34.530
- Yeah, I'm coming.
- Get the fuck off the walls.

13:34.706 --> 13:36.765
Shut the fuck up and come on.

13:36.941 --> 13:39.501
Shit. Come on.

13:40.478 --> 13:44.208
Ramos.
Turn the power off from there down.

13:44.381 --> 13:45.439
What?

13:45.615 --> 13:47.914
Turn the power off from there down!

13:48.086 --> 13:50.213
Okay, I got it!

13:52.957 --> 13:54.754
My fucking lucky day.

13:57.595 --> 14:01.121
Shit.
What the fuck is wrong with you, man?

14:16.779 --> 14:20.738
<i>Pelham 123 to Rail Control Center.
Do you read me?</i>

14:23.085 --> 14:24.780
Yes, I read you, Pelham 123.

14:24.954 --> 14:27.718
This is Control Center. Who is this?

14:28.791 --> 14:32.658
It's me, man. I didn't wanna call
till everything was ready.

14:32.827 --> 14:35.387
- It's not Jerry.
- I don't know who it is.

14:37.499 --> 14:39.296
I understand, I understand,
Pelham 123.

14:39.467 --> 14:40.525
Who the hell is this?

14:40.969 --> 14:42.937
This is the man
who's gonna rock this city.

14:43.104 --> 14:45.971
This is the man who's gonna
give the city a run for the money.

14:46.141 --> 14:49.167
<i>Look up. Look up at your screen
and you tell me what you see.</i>

14:49.344 --> 14:51.312
<i>You see what I've done?</i>

14:51.479 --> 14:52.503
I see it.

14:52.680 --> 14:55.706
One car is much more manageable
than 10 with the manpower I got.

14:55.884 --> 14:58.649
Motorman's gonna tell you
about it. Tell him what we got.

14:58.821 --> 15:00.482
They got hostages, lots of them.

15:00.656 --> 15:03.181
<i>- And they got machine guns.
- That's Jerry.</i>

15:03.359 --> 15:05.156
<i>- That's Jerry.
- Yeah, that's right.</i>

15:05.327 --> 15:06.988
Check me,
do you understand that?

15:08.531 --> 15:09.896
I check, I understand.

15:12.334 --> 15:13.858
Didn't I tell you to knock first?

15:15.004 --> 15:18.030
<i>Good, because this is what we call
a cash transaction.</i>

15:18.207 --> 15:20.607
Now, you understand commodities,
don't you?

15:21.042 --> 15:23.738
You know, pork bellies?
Gold? Light crude?

15:23.912 --> 15:28.372
Listen, no disrespect, but maybe I'm
not the guy you should be talking to.

15:28.550 --> 15:30.745
Oh, no, you are exactly the guy
I wanna talk to.

15:30.919 --> 15:33.615
Now, I want you to look at the ticker
and you tell me...

15:33.788 --> 15:37.188
...what is the going rate
for a New York City hostage today?

15:38.926 --> 15:42.089
<i>You think a million dollars
is too much? I do. I think it's corny.</i>

15:42.262 --> 15:44.628
Now get your calculator out.
You got one?

15:48.335 --> 15:50.929
<i>- Do you have a calculator?
- Yeah, we got one. I got one.</i>

15:51.104 --> 15:56.735
Okay, good. Add this up.
You got $526,315 and 79 cents.

15:56.909 --> 16:00.605
<i>That's 526,315. 79.</i>

16:01.980 --> 16:03.538
<i>Now, times that by 19.</i>

16:03.715 --> 16:04.909
What do you got?

16:05.083 --> 16:07.347
What is he, a goddamn accountant?

16:10.721 --> 16:12.484
- That's 10 million?
- What do you got?

16:12.923 --> 16:15.619
That comes out to 10 million
plus one cent.

16:15.793 --> 16:16.817
That is a deal.

16:16.994 --> 16:19.292
You call the mayor
and you tell him the price.

16:19.463 --> 16:23.424
<i>And then you tell him I want it in
100,000 $ 100 bills, you got that?</i>

16:23.803 --> 16:25.395
I got it. What about the one cent?

16:25.571 --> 16:27.299
Keep that, that's your broker fee.

16:27.472 --> 16:30.407
Now, I want the rest
in plain suitcases...

16:30.575 --> 16:33.703
...the kind with the wheels
and the portable handle, okay?

16:33.879 --> 16:36.973
Now, this is not a futures contract.
This is a spot trade.

16:37.148 --> 16:40.174
<i>That means there's a time limit on it.
Okay, you got that?</i>

16:40.352 --> 16:42.582
Now, what do you think
is a fair time limit?

16:45.356 --> 16:47.483
You know, I don't know.
I'm really just a guy...

16:47.658 --> 16:50.627
Come on, give me a time limit.
Give me a fair time limit.

16:53.497 --> 16:55.556
- Thursday.
- I was thinking more like an hour.

16:55.733 --> 16:57.325
Now, what's your watch say?

16:59.503 --> 17:00.594
Two-thirteen.

17:00.770 --> 17:02.534
Oh,
that's exactly what my watch says.

17:02.706 --> 17:05.868
So at 3:13, I want that money here,
motherfucker.

17:06.609 --> 17:09.407
<i>And after that, there is a late fee.</i>

17:09.579 --> 17:12.013
What do you think
that late fee is gonna be?

17:15.352 --> 17:17.147
<i>Come on, tell me what it'll be.</i>

17:17.819 --> 17:20.686
You're gonna kill the passengers?

17:20.857 --> 17:22.790
Oh, commodities
is what I start to kill.

17:22.959 --> 17:25.791
One for every minute
past the deadline I am forced to wait.

17:25.962 --> 17:27.691
They become more valuable
this way...

17:27.864 --> 17:29.388
...and still at the same price.

17:29.832 --> 17:32.300
He's underground.
He's never gonna pull this off.

17:32.468 --> 17:35.095
- Don't tell me, tell him.
- Who the hell is this guy?

17:35.270 --> 17:37.738
- I don't know who it is!
- Garber, just stay with it.

17:37.906 --> 17:39.498
What's your name?

17:39.675 --> 17:41.473
- What's your name, my man?
- My name?

17:42.045 --> 17:43.706
What's your name?

17:44.948 --> 17:46.210
Tell him?

17:47.650 --> 17:48.981
- Garber.
- Garber, okay.

17:49.152 --> 17:50.846
Now, seriously, man,
in 59 minutes...

17:51.019 --> 17:52.782
...I'm gonna start killing passengers.

17:52.955 --> 17:56.254
So my advice to you is to get on
the phone, get the mayor notified now.

17:56.692 --> 17:58.126
Listen, I mean...

17:58.294 --> 18:01.354
I'm just a civil-service employee.
I can't get ahold of the mayor.

18:01.531 --> 18:02.930
That's your problem, not mine.

18:03.099 --> 18:06.465
It's like, who's responsible for
who lives and who dies in New York?

18:06.635 --> 18:08.102
<i>That's New York City's problem.</i>

18:08.270 --> 18:12.263
Get the fuck off the radio
and notify the mayor, motherfucker!

18:14.276 --> 18:16.005
Okay.

18:25.086 --> 18:28.351
Nine months of this and I'm free.
Next mayor gets inaugurated...

18:28.522 --> 18:31.582
...I'm gonna be in Saint-Tropez
on the beach with a piÃ±a colada.

18:31.759 --> 18:34.125
I will never have to ride the subway
ever again.

18:34.295 --> 18:37.287
- Never say never, sir.
- Never.

18:37.765 --> 18:39.629
All right,
what's next for the afternoon?

18:39.899 --> 18:41.366
East Harlem Elementary at 2:30.

18:41.534 --> 18:44.059
<i>You're to read
The Cat In The Hat to the third grade.</i>

18:44.237 --> 18:47.536
Every time I go to the schools,
I get sick. They all have runny noses.

18:47.707 --> 18:51.404
Call Dr. Katz, tell him I want him
waiting at the school, with a flu shot.

19:05.558 --> 19:07.254
Mayor's office.

19:11.666 --> 19:14.065
- He's in Car 3.
- Yeah.

19:15.935 --> 19:16.959
What happened?

19:17.404 --> 19:19.338
Somebody just hijacked a 6 train.

19:19.506 --> 19:21.940
It's stopped in the tunnel
between 51 st and 42nd.

19:22.108 --> 19:24.804
Another idiot with a gun.
What do we know?

19:24.978 --> 19:27.606
It's unclear, but I have a car
waiting for us downstairs.

19:27.781 --> 19:29.338
Subway will get us there faster.

19:29.515 --> 19:31.380
All right. Let the doors close.

19:31.550 --> 19:34.111
Tell them we'll meet them
at 59th Street.

19:39.359 --> 19:41.259
Tell the conductor
this is now an express.

19:41.428 --> 19:43.589
- We're skipping the next five stops.
- What?

19:43.763 --> 19:46.196
- I gotta get to work.
- Hold on, hold on.

19:46.365 --> 19:49.425
Everybody will get where they
need to go, we'll make all the stops.

19:49.601 --> 19:52.126
Maybe he's not such a douchebag
after all, huh?

19:53.505 --> 19:54.597
Funny.

19:58.043 --> 20:00.307
Figures you'd be the one
to get a call like this.

20:00.479 --> 20:03.970
Hostage negotiation team here in five
minutes and the mayor's been notified.

20:04.148 --> 20:06.275
- You gonna tell him?
- Get the fuck out of here.

20:06.451 --> 20:08.645
My shift's over in 10 minutes.

20:08.819 --> 20:10.548
- What are you staring at?
- Your face.

20:10.721 --> 20:12.882
I'm trying to remember
for when it's not here.

20:13.056 --> 20:15.957
- You gonna start in on me?
- Right, I'm gonna start in on you.

20:16.126 --> 20:18.220
- Don't fuck this up, Garber.
- You wanna do it?

20:18.396 --> 20:19.953
It's your station, your call.

20:20.130 --> 20:22.496
- Oh, it's my call now?
- That's right. Your call.

20:22.999 --> 20:24.023
Come on.

20:29.239 --> 20:33.175
<i>Pelham 123, come in, this is
Rail Control Center. Are you there?</i>

20:33.610 --> 20:36.203
Gerber Baby boy. What's up?

20:36.912 --> 20:40.746
Garber. Just wanted to let you know
the mayor's been notified.

20:41.183 --> 20:42.377
Are they gonna pay?

20:43.219 --> 20:46.347
I don't know. I'm just the,
what'd you call me? The broker.

20:46.522 --> 20:49.423
No, no, you represent
the city of New York right now, buddy.

20:49.592 --> 20:53.152
I can tell you you're dealing with one
of the all-time bureaucracies, I know.

20:53.328 --> 20:56.388
- I mean, it takes time.
- You'd better fix the bureaucracy...

20:56.564 --> 20:59.328
...because when the time comes,
these hostages...

20:59.501 --> 21:01.992
...are gonna go real quick.

21:03.805 --> 21:06.273
You got it, you got it.
Any other demands?

21:06.441 --> 21:08.409
Yeah,
no fucking pizza for them, either.

21:08.576 --> 21:11.410
No, I mean, are you guys, like,
you know, are you terrorists?

21:11.580 --> 21:14.606
Do I sound like a terrorist?
Do I terrorize you?

21:14.784 --> 21:18.083
Actually, you don't, but I mean,
not that I ever talked to one.

21:18.254 --> 21:19.278
So...

21:19.455 --> 21:22.117
So, what, this is just about money?

21:22.291 --> 21:23.918
Oh, is there anything else?

21:24.093 --> 21:25.354
There's not dying.

21:25.527 --> 21:28.928
Yeah, well, you live, you die. You
go with the current or you fight it...

21:29.097 --> 21:30.758
<i>... you all end up
in the same place.</i>

21:30.932 --> 21:33.901
- Where's that, Jersey?
- Yeah, you watch it. I was born there.

21:34.436 --> 21:36.768
I'm just saying,
you're up in the motorman's cab.

21:36.939 --> 21:40.375
That means you're on the radio, which
means that you're an easy target.

21:40.543 --> 21:42.510
<i>You gotta know the drill.</i>

21:43.745 --> 21:45.440
I know that soon I won't be alone...

21:45.613 --> 21:49.276
...and if I'm the first to get shot,
I'm the first of many to get shot.

21:49.450 --> 21:51.543
That's correct,
but then you'd still be dead.

21:52.387 --> 21:55.618
Dead is an improvement on a lot
of things I can think of, buddy boy.

21:55.790 --> 21:57.280
Sounds like he slept with my ex.

21:59.159 --> 22:01.150
You know, we all owe God a death.

22:01.328 --> 22:05.128
And I'm a man who pays his debts.
Are you a man who pays his debts?

22:05.299 --> 22:08.393
Yeah, yeah, sure.
TV, cable, and my mortgage.

22:08.569 --> 22:12.972
- That's a little like dying once a month.
- You're married, you're a married man.

22:13.307 --> 22:14.331
Maybe.

22:14.508 --> 22:18.841
No, no, no. You're married, man.
Married men have mortgages.

22:19.679 --> 22:21.146
You got a mortgage?

22:21.314 --> 22:24.112
I don't know. Why don't you tell me,
then we'll both know?

22:24.283 --> 22:29.277
I don't know. I'm sure someone
out there loves you dearly and...

22:29.455 --> 22:31.285
<i>... you know,
would be worried about you.</i>

22:31.456 --> 22:33.253
<i>You're in the motorman's cab...</i>

22:33.425 --> 22:35.689
<i>... you got no cover,
sniper on the way.</i>

22:35.861 --> 22:38.329
Well, you know,
circumstances are my protection...

22:38.496 --> 22:41.659
...because right now, you know,
hostages are good insurance.

22:41.834 --> 22:44.359
By the way I see it,
I'm pretty well-protected.

22:47.073 --> 22:50.064
You know, this reminds me
of being in a confessional.

22:50.508 --> 22:52.032
Are you Catholic?

22:52.545 --> 22:53.944
I'm married, you're Catholic.

22:54.113 --> 22:56.172
<i>- Maybe. I don't know.
- No, you're Catholic.</i>

22:56.349 --> 22:57.543
And a good Catholic...

22:57.717 --> 23:00.208
...would know he's got
a trainload of innocent people.

23:00.386 --> 23:02.547
You don't wanna
kill innocent people, do you?

23:02.722 --> 23:05.121
A good Catholic
knows that nobody is innocent.

23:05.290 --> 23:09.090
And I'm not gonna kill all these
hostages. I'd give up my leverage.

23:12.797 --> 23:15.459
Well,
I hope you know what you're doing.

23:15.634 --> 23:19.799
It's running like a fucking Swiss watch
down here, so don't worry about it.

23:21.539 --> 23:23.200
So, what do I call you anyway?

23:24.442 --> 23:25.466
Call me Ryder.

23:26.278 --> 23:27.575
As in "train rider"?

23:27.746 --> 23:29.839
Call me Ryder, with a Y.

23:30.015 --> 23:31.141
<i>Ryder.</i>

23:33.351 --> 23:34.511
<i>I like you, Garber.</i>

23:35.353 --> 23:37.321
I do like you, man.

23:37.488 --> 23:39.479
You may be
the last friend I ever make.

23:41.025 --> 23:44.756
Well, I hope you're wrong, Mr. Ryder.
But, you know, I'm just a guy.

23:44.929 --> 23:47.090
<i>I'm just a guy
on the other end of the mic.</i>

23:48.465 --> 23:50.330
Oh, you don't think
this was meant to be?

23:50.501 --> 23:53.732
You don't think this was fate,
you and me?

23:54.637 --> 23:57.197
I don't know. Things happen
that lead to other things.

23:57.373 --> 23:59.671
And maybe this was one of them,
but that's it.

23:59.842 --> 24:03.437
I never get excited
about coincidence.

24:03.613 --> 24:06.377
Well, you got 50 fucking minutes,
so check me.

24:07.450 --> 24:08.917
All right. 50 minutes, check.

24:09.352 --> 24:11.217
And don't call me
unless you got news.

24:11.387 --> 24:14.185
- You got it.
- Motherfucker.

24:14.624 --> 24:16.023
G.B.

24:16.460 --> 24:17.688
You're fucking good, man.

24:21.864 --> 24:23.695
Okay. Move it the other way.

24:28.570 --> 24:31.971
All right, come on, move it.
The other way.

24:35.477 --> 24:38.071
Okay, now move it back a little less.

24:41.717 --> 24:43.707
Bingo. Got it.

24:44.151 --> 24:45.379
All right, we got it.

25:19.651 --> 25:22.052
- Who's talked to these jokers?
- That would be me.

25:22.222 --> 25:24.053
Yeah, under my supervision.
Who are you?

25:24.224 --> 25:26.488
Vincent Camonetti,
NYPD Hostage Negotiation Team.

25:26.659 --> 25:28.183
John Johnson,
Chief Transportation Officer.

25:29.530 --> 25:32.693
Walter Garber.
I'm Console Dispatch, right now.

25:32.867 --> 25:34.299
What can you tell me, Walter?

25:34.734 --> 25:36.531
His name is Ryder, with a Y.

25:36.703 --> 25:40.332
And he's asking
for $ 10 million by 3:13.

25:40.507 --> 25:44.637
Looking toward the future. Say what
he'd do if he doesn't get the money?

25:44.811 --> 25:47.371
He said he'd kill a passenger
every minute we go over.

25:47.547 --> 25:49.912
- Starting at 3:13 p. m.?
- 3-1-3, yes, sir.

25:50.082 --> 25:51.880
- Anything else?
- He's smart.

25:52.052 --> 25:54.782
If he's smart, why is he doing
something so fucking stupid?

25:54.954 --> 25:57.184
- On the train radio?
- We can get him right here.

25:57.357 --> 25:59.518
Any chance that we can get
a signal down there?

25:59.692 --> 26:01.557
We'd like to get him
on one of our cells.

26:01.728 --> 26:03.662
No,
there's no chance, not where he is.

26:04.697 --> 26:06.994
What's this?
"Leverage, spot trade"?

26:07.166 --> 26:10.033
Yeah, it's weird. He's like
a money guy, like a Wall Street.

26:10.202 --> 26:13.933
He talked about the passengers
like they were commodities.

26:14.106 --> 26:16.199
- "Catholic"?
- Yeah, I think he's Catholic.

26:16.375 --> 26:19.902
For chrissakes, Garber, you gonna tell
us what his zodiac sign is now?

26:20.079 --> 26:21.979
I'm just saying I think he's Catholic.

26:22.147 --> 26:25.411
Man asked me about "Catholic."
I wrote it down. I'm giving my opinion.

26:25.583 --> 26:27.346
Unlike other people,
I have an opinion.

26:27.518 --> 26:29.748
Fellas, can we settle
this dispute later?

26:29.921 --> 26:31.980
- Absolutely.
- Why do you think he's Catholic?

26:32.156 --> 26:35.614
I think he's Catholic because he talked
about original sin and confessions.

26:35.793 --> 26:38.057
I wrote it down.
I didn't know what else to do.

26:38.229 --> 26:39.889
- Did he ask for a priest?
- No.

26:40.063 --> 26:41.724
Good. Anything else?

26:43.500 --> 26:47.597
He sounded, the way he was talking,
he sounded like he's not afraid to die.

26:48.639 --> 26:49.901
Yeah, well, it's early yet.

26:51.275 --> 26:53.368
- The calls are coming through...?
- Right here.

26:53.544 --> 26:55.512
You hit the blue button,
you can reach him.

26:55.680 --> 26:58.011
- He'll come back to you.
- Mind if I take your seat?

26:58.181 --> 27:00.581
- No, no, go right ahead.
- Thank you, Walter.

27:00.750 --> 27:01.774
You're welcome.

27:01.952 --> 27:04.716
This is the six wire.
You don't have to touch that one.

27:04.888 --> 27:06.412
- Okay.
- That goes around the room.

27:06.590 --> 27:07.818
- Six wire.
- Why don't you...

27:07.991 --> 27:10.084
Just hit the talk here
and then that mutes it.

27:10.260 --> 27:12.353
Take the rest of the day off.
Get out of here.

27:12.529 --> 27:15.053
I thought I'd stick around,
just make sure that...

27:15.231 --> 27:19.691
Well, that wasn't a suggestion.
So why don't you go home?

27:22.771 --> 27:24.136
All right.

27:25.474 --> 27:28.411
This is it. You got all the information
over here about the 313.

27:28.579 --> 27:31.445
- Wait for his call.
- You want me to work it up right now?

27:31.615 --> 27:35.107
You call headquarters, let them know
that I'm here and I'm on the job. Okay.

27:48.731 --> 27:50.426
I gotta take a piss.

27:50.599 --> 27:51.827
So who's stopping you?

27:52.001 --> 27:56.802
All right. We wouldn't wanna end up
on any Amnesty International lists...

27:56.972 --> 27:59.532
...so step up to the door, face out.

27:59.708 --> 28:01.608
Open the middle door.

28:02.377 --> 28:04.174
Do what you gotta do.

28:06.582 --> 28:08.277
Can I jump down there?

28:20.728 --> 28:23.094
- You gotta go or don't you?
- I do, I gotta go.

28:24.299 --> 28:27.462
Step up, my man. Let's go, let's go.

28:37.276 --> 28:40.074
That kid's going places.
All right, close the doors.

28:40.246 --> 28:41.611
<i>Pelham 123, come in.</i>

28:41.781 --> 28:45.478
<i>- Pelham 123, please come in.
- All right, everybody, sit down!</i>

28:56.761 --> 28:57.785
Who is this?

28:57.963 --> 29:01.900
This is Lieutenant Camonetti. I'm with
the NYPD Hostage Negotiation Team.

29:02.068 --> 29:04.730
I'd like to talk to you
about the situation that we're in.

29:04.904 --> 29:06.394
Where the fuck is Garber?

29:06.572 --> 29:08.130
Mr. Garber is a train dispatcher.

29:08.307 --> 29:11.366
- This is now a police matter.
- Yeah, well, I wanna talk to Garber.

29:11.543 --> 29:15.570
I'm sorry, Mr. Ryder,
but Mr. Garber is no longer involved.

29:16.815 --> 29:18.305
Motorman, up!

29:19.884 --> 29:21.579
- Put Garber on.
- To be honest...

29:21.753 --> 29:23.312
...Mr. Garber has gone home.

29:23.489 --> 29:25.979
Put Garber on the fucking line
or I kill the motorman.

29:27.892 --> 29:31.954
I guarantee you I am the best person
for you to be talking to right now.

29:32.131 --> 29:33.860
Give me a moment
and I'll explain why.

29:34.400 --> 29:37.028
You were always
gonna be the first one to go.

29:37.470 --> 29:38.562
Oh, Jesus!

29:39.438 --> 29:41.099
Jesus.

29:44.743 --> 29:45.767
Mr. Camonetti...

29:45.944 --> 29:48.777
...you got 60 fucking seconds
before I kill another.

29:48.947 --> 29:52.576
- Okay? Fifty-nine, 58, 57...
- Get him. Just get Garber.

29:52.751 --> 29:55.379
- Fifty-six, 55, 54...
- We're trying to locate Garber...

29:55.553 --> 29:57.544
...ASAP, Mr. Ryder.
Why did you do that?

29:57.722 --> 30:01.282
Mr. Camonetti or whatever
fucking greaseball name you got...

30:01.458 --> 30:03.858
...the city of fucking New York
killed Jerry, okay?

30:04.028 --> 30:07.225
<i>Fifty-three, 52, 51...</i>

30:10.968 --> 30:12.196
Garber. Garber!

30:12.369 --> 30:15.826
Garber, he killed Jerry Pollard, man.

30:16.005 --> 30:18.599
Come on,
he wants to talk to you right now.

30:20.043 --> 30:21.442
He's here. He's on the way.

30:22.712 --> 30:27.081
Eleven, 10, nine, eight, seven...

30:27.250 --> 30:32.983
- He's approaching the desk.
- Six, five, four, three, two, one...

30:33.155 --> 30:34.622
Hey, it's me, it's Garber.

30:34.991 --> 30:37.323
Garber! You didn't say goodbye.

30:39.262 --> 30:40.286
You killed Jerry?

30:40.463 --> 30:43.558
No, the city of fucking New York
killed Jerry, okay?

30:43.734 --> 30:47.727
<i>The biggest rathole
in the world fucking killed Jerry.</i>

30:47.904 --> 30:50.805
Okay? Now you can
chalk another victim up to NYC.

30:50.973 --> 30:54.101
- Now, can everybody hear me?
- Yeah, we hear you, loud and clear.

30:54.277 --> 30:56.074
Now you don't have to tell
the cops...

30:56.245 --> 31:00.238
...they don't tell me how to do it or how
it's gonna be. I fucking tell them.

31:00.416 --> 31:02.213
Don't you ever, ever
leave me again.

31:02.385 --> 31:05.046
Or I'll just have to hunt you down
and I'll kill you.

31:05.220 --> 31:07.848
Now, you got 39...

31:08.457 --> 31:10.948
Thirty-nine minutes. Check me.

31:11.793 --> 31:12.919
Thirty-nine, check.

31:22.770 --> 31:25.295
This is Staley to ESU 2.
What's your position?

31:25.473 --> 31:27.964
ESU 2 approaching hostage car
from south tunnel.

31:28.409 --> 31:29.671
Go, go, go.

31:31.779 --> 31:34.805
Ten-million dollars. I'll write him
a check and get it over with.

31:34.982 --> 31:38.383
- He wants it in cash.
- I was joking, LaSalle.

31:39.019 --> 31:41.613
But we've been given one hour
to get the money together.

31:41.789 --> 31:44.223
Ten-million dollars.
Where do they get these numbers?

31:44.392 --> 31:46.553
Actually, 10 is the limit, sir.

31:46.727 --> 31:47.751
Why is that?

31:47.928 --> 31:51.193
Request to the City Controller,
he forwards it to one of our lenders...

31:51.365 --> 31:55.391
...cash gets released to the Federal
Reserve. Limit at any time is 10 million.

31:55.568 --> 31:58.230
Some idiot with a gun
wouldn't know that. I didn't know.

31:58.405 --> 32:01.239
- Well, you're very busy, sir.
- How do you know that?

32:02.743 --> 32:04.335
Here he is.

32:04.545 --> 32:07.480
- Henry, what's the situation?
- They killed a hostage.

32:07.648 --> 32:09.674
These guys may be the real deal.

32:09.851 --> 32:11.841
I thought there was one idiot
with a gun.

32:12.019 --> 32:14.715
Multiple gunmen. They're not sure.
They've got 18 hostages.

32:14.889 --> 32:18.120
They'll kill more in an hour. That's
the limit. They want you to know.

32:18.292 --> 32:19.816
- What do we know?
- Not amateurs.

32:19.994 --> 32:21.723
They cut out a car,
stopped on a rise.

32:21.896 --> 32:23.921
They can see us coming
100 yards either way.

32:24.098 --> 32:25.565
How long to get the money?

32:25.733 --> 32:26.893
- I don't know.
- Find out.

32:27.067 --> 32:30.661
- You're not thinking of paying, are you?
- I'm thinking of time and being ready.

32:30.837 --> 32:32.828
Call the Controller.
Tell them we'll pay.

32:35.241 --> 32:37.607
What's with you and Garber, huh?
Tell me about him.

32:37.776 --> 32:38.902
Scheduled to work today?

32:39.077 --> 32:41.272
- Yeah, absolutely. But...
- But what?

32:41.447 --> 32:44.279
He's only had this particular job
for a couple weeks now.

32:44.449 --> 32:47.077
- Well, why is that?
- Well, he's under investigation.

32:47.251 --> 32:48.513
What?

32:48.686 --> 32:51.678
- We were gonna suspend him...
- What's he being investigated for?

32:54.892 --> 32:57.690
He went to Japan. He had to take
a look at some new trains...

32:57.862 --> 32:59.955
...and the allegation
is that he took a bribe.

33:00.131 --> 33:01.791
Took a bribe?
Does he have a record?

33:01.965 --> 33:03.364
- Not that I know.
- You sure?

33:03.533 --> 33:05.967
Yeah, yeah. I don't think so.
I gotta take this.

33:06.169 --> 33:09.366
<i>The identity of the hijackers
is still unclear.</i>

33:09.539 --> 33:13.635
<i>The Hostage Negotiation Team has
just arrived at MTA headquarters...</i>

33:13.810 --> 33:16.745
<i>... to determine
if this is a terrorist enterprise.</i>

33:17.447 --> 33:20.280
Is that what we are? An enterprise?

33:22.052 --> 33:23.280
We're an enterprise.

33:27.324 --> 33:31.693
Well, pilot reports
that the aircraft has begun its descent.

33:37.967 --> 33:40.801
This is Staley to ESU 4.
What's your ETA?

33:40.971 --> 33:43.735
Approximately two minutes
south of target.

33:44.342 --> 33:46.503
Why is the train called
Pelham 123?

33:47.111 --> 33:49.636
Comes out of Pelham Bay
at 1:23 in the afternoon.

33:50.413 --> 33:52.643
How did you end up with this call?

33:52.816 --> 33:54.750
It's a Lexington Avenue train.

33:54.918 --> 33:57.409
I got the Lexington Avenue desk.
Came through my desk.

33:57.587 --> 33:59.782
Can you think of a reason
why you'd be targeted?

33:59.956 --> 34:02.982
Someone wanna hurt you?
Something against you or something?

34:03.159 --> 34:04.387
No.

34:10.933 --> 34:12.525
You recognize his voice?

34:14.103 --> 34:18.096
No. No, as I said, it was a coincidence
it came through my desk.

34:19.507 --> 34:22.841
Did you pick this desk?
Or was it assigned to you?

34:24.478 --> 34:25.844
Did I...?

34:26.014 --> 34:28.983
I said, did you pick this desk
or was it assigned to you?

34:35.324 --> 34:36.723
Can I take my coat off?

34:40.295 --> 34:41.489
Doesn't make any sense.

34:41.663 --> 34:43.391
- What doesn't?
- Guy you're talking to.

34:43.565 --> 34:46.898
He ain't a train dispatcher.
Walter Garber.

34:47.068 --> 34:49.059
- He's a big shot.
- Big shot at what?

34:49.237 --> 34:51.398
Rail Control.
I mean, he runs things up there.

34:51.572 --> 34:54.235
- At least he did before I went up.
- His name is Walter?

34:54.409 --> 34:55.739
Yeah.

34:57.077 --> 35:00.046
Dude like that
shouldn't be answering the phone.

35:05.586 --> 35:08.350
- Mr. Ryder wants to talk to you.
- Right.

35:08.522 --> 35:11.423
Are you sure you don't have
some sort of relationship with him?

35:11.592 --> 35:16.028
I assure you, whatever relationship
I have with him is better than yours.

35:16.195 --> 35:19.097
Jerry, my friend, was killed
while you were talking to Ryder.

35:19.266 --> 35:21.791
Maybe that's a question
you ask yourself instead of me.

35:21.969 --> 35:23.903
I didn't have anything to do
with this.

35:24.071 --> 35:26.767
But what I have in you,
Mr. Garber, is an unknown variable.

35:26.940 --> 35:29.464
- Unknown variable?
- Right. People's lives are at stake.

35:29.642 --> 35:31.109
- I understand that.
- Excuse me...

35:31.277 --> 35:33.609
...if I try to get more comfortable
with you, okay?

35:34.413 --> 35:36.506
It ain't working, but okay.

35:37.316 --> 35:38.647
Now, with that in mind...

35:38.818 --> 35:42.379
...would you agree
to a consensual search of your house?

35:42.555 --> 35:44.546
Take me 40, 45 minutes
to get a warrant.

35:46.492 --> 35:48.050
What...

35:50.196 --> 35:51.458
Yes, okay.

35:55.202 --> 35:56.533
Got him.

35:57.337 --> 35:59.737
Walter Garber, right there.

36:00.240 --> 36:02.367
No shit, look at this.

36:06.078 --> 36:09.047
- Guy took a bribe, man.
- Yeah.

36:10.216 --> 36:11.240
Baby!

36:21.793 --> 36:24.455
ESU 2, this is Staley.
What's your overall status?

36:24.629 --> 36:26.096
All positions secured.

36:26.264 --> 36:28.789
<i>All right,
hold your fire until instructed.</i>

36:35.407 --> 36:37.567
Pelham 123, can you hear me?

36:38.008 --> 36:39.839
Yeah, loud and clear, back at you.

36:40.010 --> 36:42.478
All right,
the mayor has agreed to pay...

36:42.646 --> 36:45.080
...and they're getting the money
together right now.

36:45.249 --> 36:46.273
<i>Good.</i>

36:46.450 --> 36:50.112
Well, you know, you got 28 minutes,
so I advise him to make haste.

36:50.553 --> 36:53.283
- I'm sure he will.
- So is your first name Walter?

36:54.524 --> 36:56.515
- Excuse me?
- Your name, is it Walter?

36:59.062 --> 37:00.324
<i>- Yes, it is.
- Good.</i>

37:00.496 --> 37:02.293
What are you doing
dispatching trains?

37:02.465 --> 37:05.263
I thought you were some sort of
MTA big shot.

37:05.568 --> 37:09.367
I work for the MTA.
Today they put me at dispatch...

37:10.672 --> 37:11.697
...and my bad luck.

37:11.874 --> 37:13.865
I thought you didn't
believe in bad luck.

37:14.043 --> 37:16.409
I said I didn't believe in fate.

37:16.579 --> 37:19.309
Do you believe in
rigged contracts for new trains?

37:20.783 --> 37:23.775
Look, what are
we talking about this for?

37:23.953 --> 37:26.853
- I need to know who I'm dealing with.
- You need to know who...?

37:27.022 --> 37:31.118
Yeah, I want to know who I'm dealing
with. I mean, are you a bad penny?

37:31.326 --> 37:32.793
Let me explain something to you.

37:33.762 --> 37:35.730
Being accused of something
is one thing.

37:35.897 --> 37:38.525
Being guilty of it
is something entirely different.

37:38.700 --> 37:42.100
Well, agreed. But you gotta
take me through this, my man.

37:42.269 --> 37:46.035
You got to tell me from the top.
This whole train thing. Come on.

37:50.278 --> 37:52.371
All right,
I started out in maintenance.

37:52.547 --> 37:55.744
Platform maintenance,
track maintenance, flagman...

37:56.451 --> 37:58.214
<i>...conductor.
- Conductor, really?</i>

37:59.120 --> 38:01.020
Yeah. And then motorman.

38:01.188 --> 38:03.179
A motorman.
How long did you do that for?

38:03.858 --> 38:05.257
I drove them over six years.

38:05.426 --> 38:08.418
I went to tower operations,
assistant dispatcher, dispatcher.

38:08.596 --> 38:09.620
<i>I finally ended up...</i>

38:09.797 --> 38:13.460
Yeah, you're assistant chief
transportation officer or something.

38:13.634 --> 38:17.034
- Right?
- That's right.

38:17.670 --> 38:21.606
And part of my job is to go out
to the manufacturers, you know...

38:21.775 --> 38:26.337
<i>... the people who build the trains
and bid on contracts for the trains.</i>

38:26.513 --> 38:28.038
Is that where you took the bribe?

38:28.215 --> 38:30.980
The Japanese train
over the Canadian train?

38:31.153 --> 38:35.350
I did not take a bribe, all right?
I was accused of taking a bribe.

38:35.523 --> 38:37.991
I have not been proven guilty yet.

38:38.159 --> 38:40.559
They haven't said yet.
I mean, they haven't decided.

38:40.728 --> 38:45.131
Well, they got no proof. I don't care
what they decide. It doesn't matter...

38:45.299 --> 38:46.960
Then is this
when they demoted you?

38:47.134 --> 38:50.125
That's correct. They demoted me,
pending the outcome.

38:50.303 --> 38:53.067
And now they're trying
to humiliate you, is that right?

38:53.239 --> 38:54.900
Motherfuckers.

38:55.074 --> 38:57.167
<i>Look, I know
how these things work, man, okay?</i>

38:57.343 --> 38:59.607
<i>Everything doesn't seem
to appear like what it is.</i>

38:59.779 --> 39:02.111
But you've gotta be
completely honest with me, man.

39:02.282 --> 39:04.977
