45:21.481 --> 45:22.573
You got a plan?

45:23.283 --> 45:24.648
I thought you'd have one.

45:31.924 --> 45:33.824
Because I'm some
tough-looking black guy?

45:34.927 --> 45:37.487
I saw that ring on your finger.

45:43.301 --> 45:44.791
That was a long time ago.

45:44.969 --> 45:47.597
- Okay?
- My husband had one just like it.

45:54.512 --> 45:55.843
<i>A severe sell-off underway...</i>

45:56.013 --> 45:59.277
<i>... the Dow is down 450 points
in very heavy trading...</i>

45:59.449 --> 46:01.781
<i>... as Wall Street reacts
to the terrorist attack...</i>

46:01.952 --> 46:04.887
<i>... of the New York City
subway system.</i>

46:11.762 --> 46:15.128
- How's my hair look?
- Fine. You ready to make a statement?

46:15.298 --> 46:17.324
When I have something to tell them.

46:17.501 --> 46:19.128
It's a leadership moment, sir.

46:19.303 --> 46:22.137
I'm not running for re-election,
for fucking president.

46:22.307 --> 46:24.537
I left my Rudy Giuliani suit at home.

46:24.710 --> 46:28.043
You're being selfish.
It'll take 30 seconds to reassure them.

46:35.519 --> 46:36.577
- Over there!
- Mr. Mayor!

46:36.754 --> 46:40.019
- Mr. Mayor! Mr. Mayor!
- Will you be making a statement?

46:40.191 --> 46:43.217
We're doing everything
the situation demands.

46:43.394 --> 46:46.261
I'm not gonna speculate right now.
All right?

46:46.430 --> 46:48.590
- Mayor, is it terrorism?
- No.

46:49.032 --> 46:50.624
Hey.

46:50.800 --> 46:52.700
Mayor! Are they terrorists?

46:52.869 --> 46:55.167
All right, all right, all right!

46:55.338 --> 46:57.465
Listen, nobody said anything
about terrorism...

46:57.641 --> 47:00.940
...or a bomb, anything like that.
Let's stop that right now, all right?

47:01.111 --> 47:03.875
How about your divorce? Care
to speculate how that's going?

47:04.047 --> 47:05.172
Your divorce, sir.

47:05.347 --> 47:07.247
Been a lot of talk in the news
lately...

47:07.416 --> 47:11.284
...that you have extramarital problems.
Your divorce, sir!

47:13.022 --> 47:14.717
Put it on channel 15.

47:14.890 --> 47:18.155
We got a girl in Brooklyn watching it
on her boyfriend's computer.

47:18.327 --> 47:20.386
- It's on the damn Internet.
- What?

47:22.797 --> 47:24.458
Hold on.

47:25.466 --> 47:27.331
- Son of a bitch.
- That's Ramos, isn't it?

47:27.502 --> 47:28.594
That's Phil Ramos.

47:28.770 --> 47:30.203
- Yes, it is.
- Who's Phil Ramos?

47:30.371 --> 47:34.102
He was a motorman. He killed a
couple of passengers 10 years ago?

47:34.275 --> 47:38.075
High on cough syrup, ran into the
platform, went to jail for manslaughter.

47:38.246 --> 47:39.907
Phil Ramos, I want everything.

47:40.081 --> 47:43.448
Prison time, known associates, the
works. Looks like it's from the floor.

47:43.618 --> 47:46.280
- Should the Internet be working there?
- No. No way.

47:46.454 --> 47:48.922
Maybe that's how he knows about you.
He Googled you.

47:49.090 --> 47:50.751
Or maybe Ramos told him,
who knows?

47:54.128 --> 47:56.995
Goddamn, it's the mayor.
Hello, Your Honor.

48:00.268 --> 48:02.463
Do me a favor,
forget about those guys.

48:02.637 --> 48:03.729
Easy for you to say.

48:03.905 --> 48:05.600
You rather be
one of those hostages?

48:05.773 --> 48:06.865
No.

48:07.041 --> 48:10.135
Listen up, I'll give you a crash course
on hostage negotiating.

48:10.311 --> 48:11.971
We're like rodeo clowns.

48:12.145 --> 48:15.673
We keep the bull from focusing on
what he'd like to do. Which is what?

48:15.850 --> 48:17.181
- Kill a cowboy.
- Exactly.

48:17.352 --> 48:19.820
Now, he's got his deadline.
You slow things down.

48:19.987 --> 48:23.855
Preservation of life. That's our mission.
Guy's already proven he's serious.

48:24.025 --> 48:26.084
Next deadline's gonna give
a chance again.

48:26.260 --> 48:29.023
- How do we deal with that?
- Get the money there on time.

48:29.196 --> 48:31.630
If we don't, we pretend
the deadline doesn't exist...

48:31.798 --> 48:33.925
...talk through it, we buy time,
get movement.

48:34.101 --> 48:35.466
- Movement?
- That's right.

48:35.635 --> 48:39.469
Contradicts himself, inconsistency in
his demand, you got some movement.

48:39.639 --> 48:43.200
- Right.
- All right, let's go out there.

48:45.845 --> 48:47.312
<i>This was the scene
moments ago...</i>

48:47.480 --> 48:49.812
<i>... outside the Rail Control Center
in Midtown.</i>

48:49.982 --> 48:52.212
<i>I'm not gonna speculate right now.</i>

48:52.385 --> 48:54.650
That is a beautiful suit
he's got there.

48:57.691 --> 49:00.659
Can't get it out of my head.
I'm gonna die today.

49:01.827 --> 49:06.662
Visualization's a very powerful thing.
You keep thinking it, you never know.

49:19.643 --> 49:22.407
Please let it be me
who drops this motherfucker.

49:29.086 --> 49:31.146
Hey, Garber. You there, buddy?

49:33.324 --> 49:34.722
Yeah, I'm here.

49:34.892 --> 49:37.087
<i>A little birdie told me
the mayor walked in.</i>

49:37.261 --> 49:38.558
Can I talk to him?

49:41.398 --> 49:43.764
<i>- Can he hear me?
- How does he know I'm here?</i>

49:45.335 --> 49:47.599
- Does he have a camera in here?
- Can he hear me?

49:47.771 --> 49:51.831
We can, we can, we can...
We can all hear you here. Yes.

49:52.008 --> 49:56.707
Okay, good. So tell him...
Tell him I wanna make him a deal.

49:57.480 --> 49:59.744
<i>Tell him I'll make him a deal
right now.</i>

49:59.916 --> 50:01.508
Okay, all right.

50:01.684 --> 50:03.276
Well, come on, speak up,
Mr. Mayor.

50:03.453 --> 50:05.250
You're talking to your constituents.

50:05.421 --> 50:08.912
We got a train full
of registered voters. Don't you care?

50:09.090 --> 50:11.685
Don't you care about your voters?

50:13.329 --> 50:16.389
This is not a good idea.
Don't talk. Don't engage with him.

50:16.566 --> 50:19.228
I know what I'm doing,
I've been doing this a long time.

50:19.403 --> 50:20.597
<i>Come on, buddy, speak up.</i>

50:20.771 --> 50:23.466
You gotta hit the blue button there,
Your Honor.

50:25.107 --> 50:26.472
Yes, this is the mayor.

50:26.909 --> 50:29.139
Hey. Good to meet you, man.

50:29.312 --> 50:31.712
And listen, tell me this, is this true?

50:31.881 --> 50:33.212
I read that you make, like...

50:33.382 --> 50:37.011
<i>... one dollar a year to be a mayor
of New York, is that true?</i>

50:37.186 --> 50:39.484
Yes, but at least it's honest work.

50:39.655 --> 50:43.249
After taxes that's, like,
87 cents, isn't it?

50:43.425 --> 50:44.449
Yes.

50:44.626 --> 50:45.991
Don't bullshit me, man.

50:46.161 --> 50:50.291
It would take, like, 3000 years
to pay off that suit that you're wearing.

50:50.465 --> 50:53.366
What do you got, 20, 30 million
dollars or something like that?

50:53.535 --> 50:56.436
You don't get that without screwing
someone, screwing everyone.

50:56.604 --> 50:58.731
I'm sure your wife knows
something about that.

51:03.577 --> 51:05.102
You said you had a deal for me.

51:05.280 --> 51:07.111
Yeah, I do.
I wanna make you a deal.

51:07.282 --> 51:09.409
I wanna tell you
you could come down here...

51:09.584 --> 51:13.610
...and I will trade you for all these
passengers in the train, how's that?

51:17.458 --> 51:21.519
Okay, you could save the lives
of 17 New Yorkers.

51:21.695 --> 51:23.595
Now, that's a good deal.

51:26.233 --> 51:27.461
<i>What do you think?</i>

51:31.972 --> 51:33.462
Give us a moment.

51:33.641 --> 51:35.370
Okay.

51:35.809 --> 51:37.777
I'll give you a moment.

51:40.114 --> 51:42.742
You turn this into a circus,
gonna get someone killed.

51:42.917 --> 51:45.477
Now, you entered his world, exit it.

51:50.857 --> 51:54.418
Okay, time's up. What's the deal?

51:54.694 --> 51:57.458
It's a nice offer, but I'm afraid
I'm gonna have to decline.

51:57.630 --> 52:00.690
Good. Because if you begged me,
I wouldn't give you that deal, man.

52:00.867 --> 52:03.664
You think anyone cares about
a philandering asshole like you?

52:03.835 --> 52:06.827
New York would love me to
pull the fucking trigger on you.

52:07.005 --> 52:10.566
Hey, Garber. This is the... This is
the guy that's trying to get rid of you.

52:10.742 --> 52:12.676
- Keep talking.
- Do you believe this shit?

52:12.844 --> 52:14.539
<i>- Calm...
- You don't think he...</i>

52:14.713 --> 52:16.180
...broke the same rules
we broke?

52:16.348 --> 52:18.179
- He knows it, I know it.
- Calm him down.

52:18.350 --> 52:19.873
<i>- All right...
- He can eat shit.</i>

52:20.051 --> 52:21.484
- Calm him down.
- You're...

52:21.652 --> 52:23.517
<i>- You're breaking up.
- He can kiss my ass!</i>

52:23.688 --> 52:25.714
I like the deal.
It's a good deal, but...

52:25.891 --> 52:27.222
<i>Fuck you, Mr. Mayor!</i>

52:27.392 --> 52:31.021
Now, I want my fucking money now!
You understand me? Now!

52:31.196 --> 52:34.131
- Just tell him the money's on the way.
- The money's on the way.

52:34.299 --> 52:36.823
Because he's, like,
a used-car salesman, this asshole.

52:37.001 --> 52:39.368
He can lick my bunghole,
motherfucker!

52:40.205 --> 52:42.730
One mistake
and everyone has something to say.

52:43.442 --> 52:44.704
Was she worth it?

52:44.876 --> 52:48.608
Yes. You have nine minutes.
How are you gonna get the money?

52:48.781 --> 52:52.046
They're shutting down every
intersection here to Brooklyn.

53:00.225 --> 53:02.090
Phil Ramos, male, Hispanic, 39.

53:02.260 --> 53:04.421
Sentenced two to four years
for manslaughter...

53:04.596 --> 53:06.564
...paroled last month from Clinton.

53:06.732 --> 53:09.928
